1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 13=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:42,030 --> 00:00:43,030
What was that sound?

4
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:45,710
No idea.

5
00:00:58,640 --> 00:00:59,750
In such a big operation,

6
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:01,430
nothing came of it.

7
00:01:02,070 --> 00:01:03,103
What kind of deal is that?

8
00:01:04,310 --> 00:01:05,840
This is your first Chinese tomb.

9
00:01:05,850 --> 00:01:06,929
Being able to run into this

10
00:01:06,940 --> 00:01:08,030
already means you are lucky.

11
00:01:08,510 --> 00:01:10,710
Getting nothing is considered lucky?

12
00:01:11,230 --> 00:01:12,590
If I came out loaded with treasure,

13
00:01:12,870 --> 00:01:14,280
would that mean I'm extremely lucky?

14
00:01:14,710 --> 00:01:16,280
We enter tombs to satisfy curiosity

15
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:17,480
and the urge for adventure.

16
00:01:17,870 --> 00:01:19,310
What are burial items anyway?

17
00:01:19,670 --> 00:01:21,419
Even if the He Shi Bi
were placed before me,

18
00:01:21,430 --> 00:01:22,350
if I feel tempted,

19
00:01:22,361 --> 00:01:23,680
you can have the vajra talisman.

20
00:01:23,870 --> 00:01:24,760
So noble?

21
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,600
Of course.

22
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,840
I carry a mission.

23
00:01:29,230 --> 00:01:30,590
Archaeological research

24
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:33,640
values the strangest tombs the most.

25
00:01:35,510 --> 00:01:36,480
If that is the case,

26
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,870
tell me

27
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:39,590
your latest discovery

28
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,510
about the nether tomb.

29
00:01:43,590 --> 00:01:44,680
There is a theory.

30
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,510
Exquisite objects contain

31
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,560
the countless efforts of craftsmen.

32
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:51,000
Over time, they gain spiritual energy.

33
00:01:51,230 --> 00:01:52,350
Even if they no longer exist,

34
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:54,000
their souls remain.

35
00:01:54,230 --> 00:01:56,120
Like the ghost ships
you talk about overseas.

36
00:01:56,406 --> 00:01:57,366
They sank in a shipwreck

37
00:01:57,377 --> 00:01:59,353
and have lain at the bottom
of the sea for years,

38
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:01,400
yet people still claim
to see them occasionally.

39
00:02:02,430 --> 00:02:06,000
Inside the nether tomb,
there is also a mysterious force field.

40
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,710
That is called the tomb soul.

41
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:12,630
I thought you were a firm materialist.

42
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:15,190
I didn't expect you to believe this.

43
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:17,030
I never said I believed it.

44
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:21,150
Just like what we encountered.

45
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:23,000
One tomb with two chambers.

46
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,360
After tomb raiders enter,

47
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,360
they see another tomb inside a tomb.

48
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,080
Such an unbelievable situation

49
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,430
naturally makes no sense.

50
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,520
In the end, rumors distort the truth,

51
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,800
so it becomes the nether tomb.

52
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,520
Xing, Xing.

53
00:02:59,573 --> 00:03:00,756
Huang asked you to wrap it up.

54
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:01,640
Reply asap.

55
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,680
Over.

56
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,680
So many people here.

57
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,360
Huang.

58
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:09,680
Huzi and Xing are not responding.

59
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:12,120
Those two probably think
it is cool inside

60
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,280
and don't want to come out.

61
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:14,920
Lu,

62
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:15,800
give me the gun.

63
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,590
Chubby, take care of Lu.

64
00:03:17,590 --> 00:03:18,430
Be careful.

65
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:30,430
Xiaolong stays. Everyone else, chase!

66
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:32,150
Yes. Chase!

67
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,080
Hurry.

68
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,400
Stop right there.

69
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:52,920
Hurry.

70
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:56,840
This way.

71
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:58,310
Stop.

72
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,200
Stop running.

73
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:11,750
Stop running.

74
00:04:16,270 --> 00:04:17,110
Lu,

75
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:19,310
I just thought of a great idea.

76
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,320
What idea?

77
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:27,400
Don't move.

78
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,040
You jerk.

79
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:32,190
That is beyond wicked.

80
00:04:32,470 --> 00:04:33,310
Buddy,

81
00:04:33,430 --> 00:04:34,310
don't shoot.

82
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,440
Calm down.

83
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:40,110
You jerk.

84
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,560
You can't risk lives like this.

85
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,030
You are playing with my life.

86
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:45,000
Nothing ventured, nothing gained.

87
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:46,160
You are the jerk.

88
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,230
Hurry.

89
00:04:58,430 --> 00:04:59,600
The flame is getting weaker.

90
00:05:00,430 --> 00:05:01,996
That means the oxygen level is dropping.

91
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:03,680
We need to use flashlights.

92
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:28,190
How did we end up back

93
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:30,040
at the starting place again?

94
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,390
We have been walking for so long.

95
00:05:35,630 --> 00:05:37,270
Could that all have been an illusion?

96
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:40,070
Is this the real soul-locking stair?

97
00:05:40,190 --> 00:05:42,510
We did not go uphill or downhill;

98
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,870
we have been walking on a flat plane.

99
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,480
This is not an illusion.

100
00:05:48,830 --> 00:05:50,600
This is a closed circle.

101
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:54,583
At least, we know now

102
00:05:54,594 --> 00:05:56,120
we've returned to the starting point.

103
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:58,310
If you are trapped in a closed loop

104
00:05:58,310 --> 00:05:59,150
without realizing it,

105
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,480
that is the truly terrifying part.

106
00:06:09,430 --> 00:06:10,870
This tomb is really strange.

107
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:14,053
Ever since we came in,
my compass has never been accurate.

108
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:17,360
We passed through 8 burial chambers.

109
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,190
8 chambers?

110
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,430
Then they must correspond to the Bagua.

111
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:24,680
You know the Bagua?

112
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,720
Just a little.

113
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:29,390
I wouldn't dare show off
in front of you.

114
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:33,070
Knowing even a little
is already impressive.

115
00:06:36,390 --> 00:06:37,560
Then we will rely on you.

116
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:51,800
Qian, Kun, Zhun, Meng, Xu, Song, Shi.

117
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:55,000
Bi, Xiao Xu, Lyu, Tai, Pi.

118
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,310
Tong Ren, Da You, Qian, Yu, Sui.

119
00:06:56,310 --> 00:06:57,800
Gu, Lin, Guan, Shi He, Bi.

120
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,040
Bo, Fu, Wu Wang, Da Xu, Yi.

121
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,240
Da Guo, Kan, Li. Thirty done.

122
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,870
Xian, Heng, Dun, Dazhuang.

123
00:07:01,870 --> 00:07:04,750
Jin, Ming Yi, Jia Ren, Kui.

124
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,830
Could it be a changing one?

125
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,390
Song comes from Dun;
Tai becomes Gui Mei.

126
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,830
Pi follows Jian;
Sui involves three moves.

127
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:19,920
First Kun, then Shi He, and Wei Ji too.

128
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:24,040
Gu changes thrice: Bi, Jing, Ji Ji.

129
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:33,470
Did you find it?

130
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,360
No water, no food.

131
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:42,680
If we can't find an exit soon,

132
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,560
we'll end up like the phoenixes
on this wall,

133
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,800
stuck forever
in this gloomy ghost place.

134
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:51,670
Phoenixes...

135
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:57,150
This way.

136
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,600
Follow me.

137
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,560
Hurry.

138
00:08:18,510 --> 00:08:19,560
Dazhuang, Shan, Big Guy.

139
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,760
Come back with me.

140
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,070
The rest, keep chasing.

141
00:08:40,150 --> 00:08:41,120
Those jerks.

142
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:42,896
So many valuable things here.

143
00:08:43,270 --> 00:08:44,910
I'm greedy, yet I took nothing.

144
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,240
Why are you staring at that jar?

145
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:50,600
Look for the explosives.

146
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,440
Got it.

147
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,670
Hurry up.

148
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:21,750
I'll make sure you fail this time.

149
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:22,750
Xiaolong.

150
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,440
Xiaolong.

151
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:40,800
Xiaolong.

152
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:58,350
Xiaolong.

153
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,040
Xiaolong.

154
00:10:15,030 --> 00:10:15,870
Xiaolong.

155
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,550
Don't shoot.

156
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:29,480
Chubby, you jerk.

157
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:32,590
Come out.

158
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,270
I'll come out.

159
00:10:34,270 --> 00:10:35,150
Don't shoot.

160
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,550
Don't shoot.

161
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:37,590
Go back.

162
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,270
They all ran away,

163
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,720
leaving me here alone.

164
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,440
Get as far away as you can.

165
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,510
Jerks.

166
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,110
Come here.

167
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,280
Buddy.

168
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:51,240
This is utterly heartless.

169
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,720
Huang Long, I got separated.

170
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:04,670
What were you saying just now?

171
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:07,270
I was cursing Chubby.

172
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:09,000
And that vile woman,

173
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,000
He Shutong.

174
00:11:10,550 --> 00:11:12,550
She is completely treacherous.

175
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,440
She abandoned me here.

176
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,406
Where are Chen Youxi and Bai Lingling?

177
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,200
Dead.

178
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,480
After you blew that thing up,

179
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:24,360
another huge ball fell from above.

180
00:11:24,630 --> 00:11:26,320
It smashed down like that,

181
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,240
and they were turned into meat paste.

182
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:29,840
They died horribly.

183
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:31,990
And then?

184
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:33,030
Then,

185
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,870
we started digging.

186
00:11:34,870 --> 00:11:36,080
And we dug it out.

187
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,270
I said we should run home.

188
00:11:37,773 --> 00:11:38,750
But they were unwilling.

189
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:39,910
Then, He Shutong

190
00:11:39,921 --> 00:11:40,910
used a diversion tactic.

191
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,960
After that, Chubby and I...

192
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:45,120
Go on.

193
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,600
We wanted to steal some

194
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,750
of your stuff to sell.

195
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,790
We finally got our hands on it,

196
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:52,080
and the two of them ran off.

197
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:52,960
Before leaving,

198
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,240
they even kicked me.

199
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:55,550
Such jerks.

200
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:56,390
Wait.

201
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:00,120
What did you and Chubby get?

202
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,600
Well.

203
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,910
He took that thing.

204
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,480
The one placed there.

205
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,120
Where is my box?

206
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,480
The Luo Shu.

207
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,630
King Wen's Bagua diagram.

208
00:12:23,077 --> 00:12:25,477
Remember the phoenix pearl pattern
in the previous chamber?

209
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:27,670
What about it?

210
00:12:28,630 --> 00:12:30,240
All the phoenixes are different.

211
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:33,630
Their poses are different.

212
00:12:34,030 --> 00:12:36,270
Some are resting;
some are spreading their wings.

213
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:37,800
No.

214
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,150
Some have crests;

215
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:40,150
some do not.

216
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:41,720
Some have three tails;

217
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:42,600
some have two.

218
00:12:42,850 --> 00:12:43,949
Those with crests are Feng.

219
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,209
Those without crests are Huang.

220
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,719
The Feng is male; the Huang is female.

221
00:12:46,730 --> 00:12:48,009
So, they represent Yin and Yang.

222
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:49,720
Now, the pearls.

223
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,500
Although the pattern is circular,

224
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:55,120
between two pearls,
sometimes there are two Feng,

225
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:57,150
sometimes three Huang,

226
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,910
and in some cases even nine Feng.

227
00:13:02,716 --> 00:13:04,762
Huang represents Yin
and is marked as black pearls.

228
00:13:05,270 --> 00:13:07,270
If there are two Huang
between two pearls,

229
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:08,480
draw two black pearls

230
00:13:08,976 --> 00:13:10,502
and connect them with a straight line.

231
00:13:10,786 --> 00:13:12,839
Feng represents Yang
and is marked as white pearls.

232
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:15,390
If there are three Feng
between two pearls,

233
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:16,963
draw three white pearls

234
00:13:16,974 --> 00:13:18,487
and connect them with a straight line.

235
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:20,720
And so on.

236
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:26,680
Let us go.

237
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:32,480
Quick. Over here.

238
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:56,500
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

239
00:13:58,180 --> 00:14:01,860
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

240
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:07,500
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

241
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:14,650
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

242
00:14:15,210 --> 00:14:26,230
♪La la♪

243
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:34,970
♪No line divides the border♪

244
00:14:35,410 --> 00:14:37,750
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

245
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,120
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

246
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:42,810
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

247
00:14:44,310 --> 00:14:46,020
♪Hey hey hey♪

248
00:14:47,350 --> 00:14:49,170
♪Hey hey hey♪

249
00:14:51,820 --> 00:14:52,820
♪Hey hey♪

250
00:14:52,970 --> 00:14:53,970
♪Hey hey♪

251
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:56,510
♪Hey hey♪

252
00:14:58,140 --> 00:15:02,340
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

253
00:15:02,930 --> 00:15:06,640
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

254
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:11,140
♪No difference between you and me♪

255
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:13,750
♪No lead or side role on this stage♪

256
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:15,960
♪A perfect life is something we share♪

257
00:15:16,180 --> 00:15:18,460
♪Love declares across the sky and earth♪

258
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:24,180
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

259
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:29,030
♪Time and space go beyond all bounds♪

260
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:33,880
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

261
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:35,970
♪This is our world♪

262
00:15:35,970 --> 00:15:41,000
♪Shining lives bring the change♪

263
